                    <span>What's with the next review? A 1-star rant from a reviewer whose other reviews are for yoga books?  This book has sold over 100K copies in just over a year on the market, was on the BusinessWeek bestseller list for 7 months in 2004, and is one of Harvard Business School Press' best selling books. It opened up a whole new area in leadership thinking and spawned a bunch of imitiators. So what's the story? Someone with a particularly dull axe to grind?</span>
                  
